    "caption": "The mountain alarm system with a whistle loud enough to echo.",
    "shortDescription": "Marmots are large, chubby ground squirrels that live in mountain meadows and use piercing whistles to warn the whole colony the moment they spot a hawk or fox. When the whistle goes, every marmot dives for a burrow entrance at once. Fun fact: Marmots hibernate for up to eight months of the year — the longest hibernation of any mammal their size."
